caption: I stopped off here a few weeks ago while out walking and it's such a beautiful well kept church. It was also very peaceful inside even though there were alot of tourists but people were respectful.

This is a church designed by Gustave Eiffel some 20 years prior to his work on the Eiffel Tower. We enjoyed a brief look around when passing by recently.  The exterior is imposing but modest, fronted with portal and rose window and backed by a bell tower.  The interior has good lighting and space. There are nice things to see including murals upon the walls of the nave and impressive stained-glass windows.  Worth a look around if you enjoy seeing old churches during your travels.

The √âglise Notre-Dame des Sept Douleurs in Paris is a breathtaking architectural gem that embodies both historical significance and spiritual beauty. From its magnificent facade adorned with intricate details to its serene interior filled with awe-inspiring artwork and ornate decorations, every corner of this church exudes a sense of reverence and wonder. The atmosphere inside is serene and peaceful, offering visitors a tranquil escape from the bustling streets of Paris. Whether you're admiring the stunning stained glass windows, marveling at the exquisite sculptures, or simply taking a moment for quiet reflection, a visit to √âglise Notre-Dame des Sept Douleurs is sure to uplift the soul and leave a lasting impression.
